        <name>STM32_GPIO_WKUP</name>
        <initializer>(1 &lt;&lt; 8)</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Configures a GPIO pin to power on the system after Poweroff. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This flag is reserved to GPIO pins that are associated with wake-up pins in STM32 PWR devicetree node, through the property &quot;wkup-gpios&quot;. </para>
